Nigerians have reacted to the courtesy visit paid to the Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi by the Nigerian singer and rapper, Habeeb Okikiola, popularly known as Portable. The Zazuu Zeh crooner was seen on Sunday in several pictures on social media, posing with the monarch. His meeting with the king got many reactions as Nigerians were surprised to see the monarch welcome the singer into his palace. @AyourKunle wrote, “Seest thou a man,diligent in his business..he shall stand before Kings.. and not mean men.” @chaichowski wrote, “I’m afraid I don’t understand what this meeting connotes, this guy embodies no value worth humiliating, anyways, what do I know!” @abel_amegwu wrote, “Why him no act like mad person inside palace if dem no go throw am out from window.” @omo_kehinmi wrote, “Those of you with your so called good boys and girls have you been honoured by Oonirisa? Grace is working for him Zaazu. Cave your own niche stop been petty.” @RonymanNwankwo wrote, “What a world. So Portable is the standard for youths now!” POLL @Charismatic_Oba wrote, “I hope he won’t rant afterwards cos this guy no portable at all.”